elements.name: licenseCertificatePermitTypeCode
elements.description:
A code that identifies the license, certificate, permit, or ‘non-standard’ visa number reported:

  • Steel Import License.
  • Singapore TPL Certificate.
  • Canadian NAFTA TPL Certificate.
  • Mexican NAFTA TPL Certificate.
  • Beef Export Certificate.
  • Diamond Certificate.
  • Andean Drug Partnership Drug Eradication Act (ATPDEA) Certificate (HTS 98211119).
  • Australia Free Trade Export Certificate.
  • Mexican Cement Import License.
  • CAFTA TPL Certificate.
  • Atlantic Lumber Board (ALB) Certificate.
  • Cotton Shirting Fabric License.
  • Haiti Earned Import Allowance.
  • Agricultural License.
  • Canadian Softwood Lumber Permit (note: 1990’s program; no longer active).
  • Canadian Export Sugar Certificate.
  • Wool License.
  • Caribbean Basin Trade Partnership Act (CBTPA) Certification.
  • African Growth and Opportunity Act (AGOA) Textile Provision Number.
  • Other ‘Non-Standard’ Visa (not used at this time).
  • USDA Sugar Certificate.
  • Organic Product Exemption Certificate.
  • AMS Certificate of Exemption.
  • AMS US Origin Certificate (not yet available).
  • Dominican Republic Earned Allowance Program Certificate.
  • Mexican Sugar Export License.
  • General Note 15 (c) Waiver Certificate.
  • Reserved.
  • Canadian USMCA TPL Certificate.
  • Mexican USMCA TPL Certificate.

elements.name: licenseNumberCertificateNumberPermitNumber
elements.description: The identifying number or code as provided on the license, certificate, permit, or non-standard visa that corresponds to the Type Code. Left justify, space fill.

elements.name: filler1
elements.description: Space fill until expanded length fully supported. Reserved filler for future expansion of the Number when fully ACE compatible.
